1
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:04,540
This one's too dowdy

2
00:02:04,939 --> 00:02:05,939
Our old lady's stylish

3
00:02:06,299 --> 00:02:07,239
Hand me that green one

4
00:02:07,239 --> 00:02:07,719
the light green one

5
00:02:07,719 --> 00:02:08,180
This one, right?

6
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:09,120
Yeah, the pea-green one

7
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:12,520
This one's not bad

8
00:02:12,580 --> 00:02:13,060
How much?

9
00:02:13,180 --> 00:02:13,599
Forty

10
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:14,719
Okay, wrap it up

11
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:18,819
How much for these long johns?

12
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:19,780
Fifteen bucks a pair

13
00:02:19,919 --> 00:02:20,360
They're on clearance

14
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:21,259
Hasn't it been two weeks

15
00:02:21,259 --> 00:02:22,039
since the Start of Autumn?

16
00:02:22,639 --> 00:02:23,879
Those three grown kids of mine

17
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:25,460
never know to bundle up

18
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,180
Each autumn rain makes it colder

19
00:02:28,419 --> 00:02:31,180
I'll take two mediums

20
00:02:31,340 --> 00:02:31,719
You got it

21
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:33,020
These two are mediums

22
00:02:33,039 --> 00:02:33,300
Good

23
00:02:33,479 --> 00:02:36,159
Pick me an extra small too

24
00:02:36,580 --> 00:02:37,020
Hey there

25
00:02:37,439 --> 00:02:38,620
Are these gloves durable?

26
00:02:38,819 --> 00:02:39,280
Very durable

27
00:02:39,539 --> 00:02:39,960
You see

28
00:02:40,039 --> 00:02:41,919
My brother, he's someone

29
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:44,180
who works with wood all day

30
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:44,659
Sure

31
00:02:45,340 --> 00:02:46,180
Good things come in pairs

32
00:02:46,639 --> 00:02:47,360
Give me two pairs

33
00:02:48,020 --> 00:02:48,340
Okay

34
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:49,259
Hey there

35
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:50,879
How much for this maternity hat?

36
00:02:51,300 --> 00:02:51,919
Fifty-five

37
00:02:53,780 --> 00:02:55,039
Okay, wrap it up

38
00:02:55,180 --> 00:02:56,139
Take care now! You got it

39
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:56,719
Thanks

40
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:01,319
Hi, just having a look

41
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:03,400
How much is this toy car?

42
00:03:03,620 --> 00:03:04,639
Sixty-five, ma'am

43
00:03:04,979 --> 00:03:05,960
It's a blind box, right?

44
00:03:06,159 --> 00:03:06,659
That's right

45
00:03:06,819 --> 00:03:08,599
Okay, get me six of them

46
00:03:08,759 --> 00:03:09,099
Sure

47
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:10,680
And add this car too

48
00:03:23,740 --> 00:03:24,280
Here you go.

49
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:25,340
Come again soon!

50
00:03:25,699 --> 00:03:26,180
How much is this?

51
00:03:26,180 --> 00:03:26,740
What would you like?

52
00:03:26,919 --> 00:03:27,879
This one's 25.

53
00:03:28,219 --> 00:03:28,819
And this one?

54
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:29,419
Nine bucks.

55
00:03:31,580 --> 00:03:32,180
Hey, boss.

56
00:03:32,939 --> 00:03:35,580
This snakehead's 25 a pound?

57
00:03:36,439 --> 00:03:37,400
Can you go a little lower?

58
00:03:37,439 --> 00:03:38,219
How about 22 a pound?

59
00:03:39,939 --> 00:03:42,020
You don't look like you're short three bucks.

60
00:03:42,199 --> 00:03:42,699
Besides,

61
00:03:42,699 --> 00:03:44,400
it's a holiday, no haggling.

62
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:46,379
It's exactly because it's a holiday.

63
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:47,960
What business doesn't involve haggling?

64
00:03:48,099 --> 00:03:48,580
How about this?

65
00:03:49,060 --> 00:03:50,020
Let's meet halfway.

66
00:03:50,060 --> 00:03:51,680
That makes it 22.5 a pound.

67
00:03:51,860 --> 00:03:53,219
Pick me a bigger one.

68
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:54,580
Hold on—

69
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,560
It's settled then.

70
00:03:56,060 --> 00:03:56,979
Fine, fine, fine.

71
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,219
This one, then.

72
00:04:00,479 --> 00:04:00,800
Deal.

73
00:04:03,419 --> 00:04:04,520
Is that a king crab?

74
00:04:05,340 --> 00:04:06,620
Alaskan king crab!

75
00:04:07,479 --> 00:04:09,159
Don't you dare haggle on this one.

76
00:04:09,460 --> 00:04:11,020
I'll give you the wholesale price straight up.

77
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:11,939
Two hundred thirty.

78
00:04:12,699 --> 00:04:13,539
That expensive?

79
00:04:13,659 --> 00:04:14,060
Boss,

80
00:04:14,199 --> 00:04:16,300
this is an Alaskan king crab.

81
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:18,300
It flew in just this morning.

82
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:20,060
Isn't that Fanyan?

83
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:21,360
What a coincidence!

84
00:04:24,019 --> 00:04:25,540
You two, as a couple—

85
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:28,240
one minute selling fake furs online,

86
00:04:28,660 --> 00:04:29,399
the next you're into

87
00:04:29,399 --> 00:04:30,420
the seafood business.

88
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:31,600
Honestly,

89
00:04:31,819 --> 00:04:32,680
from eggs, small as they are,

90
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:33,759
to planes and missiles,

91
00:04:33,959 --> 00:04:35,279
there's nothing you two won't trade.

92
00:04:35,579 --> 00:04:37,459
W-Well, it's just to make a living, isn't it?

93
00:04:37,639 --> 00:04:38,540
Besides, the more we earn,

94
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:39,560
the better a life

95
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:40,279
our Xiaofang will have someday.

96
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,699
Don't you bring up Xiaofang to me.

97
00:04:41,959 --> 00:04:42,939
Xiaofang has nothing

98
00:04:42,939 --> 00:04:43,980
to do with your family.

99
00:04:44,220 --> 00:04:44,800
Won't mention her, won't.

100
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:46,279
So you're buying a king crab?

101
00:04:46,639 --> 00:04:47,819
Why waste your money on that?

102
00:04:47,819 --> 00:04:48,600
We've got some at home.

103
00:04:48,740 --> 00:04:49,420
I'll get one for you.

104
00:04:49,740 --> 00:04:50,959
Pick a big one, a big one.

105
00:04:51,259 --> 00:04:52,100
A small one, small, small.

106
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:56,240
Take this home to nourish Xiaofang.

107
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:57,379
Tell her it's from her father-in-law,

108
00:04:57,379 --> 00:04:58,319
just a little token of care.

109
00:04:58,459 --> 00:04:58,819
Here.

110
00:05:00,139 --> 00:05:00,579
Boss.

111
00:05:01,660 --> 00:05:03,000
That big king crab—

112
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:03,620
weigh it for me.

113
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:05,060
I'll take it at your price.

114
00:05:05,779 --> 00:05:06,439
Sure, sure.

115
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:07,860
Speak of the devil.

116
00:05:08,399 --> 00:05:09,420
Sucker.

117
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:10,879
Such a fool.

118
00:05:11,279 --> 00:05:12,480
Stop calling yourself the father-in-law.

119
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:13,879
It's no good if Xiaofang finds out.

120
00:05:15,180 --> 00:05:15,959
What's no good about it?

121
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:17,500
Let me tell you,

122
00:05:17,540 --> 00:05:19,339
I'm gonna be Xiaofang's father-in-law, no matter what.

123
00:05:19,660 --> 00:05:20,560
Then give me the money

124
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:21,300
to study painting.

125
00:05:21,579 --> 00:05:22,899
What the hell's the use of your painting?

126
00:05:22,939 --> 00:05:24,360
It earns less than selling crabs.

127
00:05:24,759 --> 00:05:25,699
Eight hundred eighty-eight.

128
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:26,839
Fine, I've thought it through.

129
00:05:26,899 --> 00:05:28,199
Since you don't want to work at the site,

130
00:05:28,220 --> 00:05:29,139
then we won't go.

131
00:05:30,079 --> 00:05:30,680
From now on,

132
00:05:30,740 --> 00:05:32,199
you'll learn the trade from your dad, me.

133
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:33,220
I'll pay you a wage.

134
00:05:34,759 --> 00:05:35,720
How much can you pay me?

135
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:36,959
By the day.

136
00:05:36,959 --> 00:05:37,980
Two hundred a day.

137
00:05:39,399 --> 00:05:39,939
Two-fifty.

138
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:41,819
Three hundred, three hundred.

139
00:05:41,819 --> 00:05:42,540
No higher than that.

140
00:05:42,819 --> 00:05:43,360
You're my son,

141
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,160
that's why I'm paying this much.

142
00:05:44,939 --> 00:05:46,000
Keep it in the family.

143
00:05:48,660 --> 00:05:49,040
All right!

144
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:50,100
Sure.

145
00:05:50,620 --> 00:05:51,259
Take care now.

146
00:05:51,620 --> 00:05:52,040
Will do!

147
00:05:53,699 --> 00:05:54,180
Look at that.

148
00:05:54,639 --> 00:05:56,459
So many people. Business is booming.

149
00:05:57,699 --> 00:05:58,600
Looks like nail salons

150
00:05:58,620 --> 00:05:59,639
really rake in the cash these days.

151
00:06:01,579 --> 00:06:02,519
Uncle's right.

152
00:06:03,079 --> 00:06:04,199
Everyone loves looking good now.

153
00:06:04,639 --> 00:06:05,600
Once we open our shop,

154
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:06,500
it'll be just as popular.

155
00:06:07,060 --> 00:06:08,100
Definitely more popular than this.

156
00:06:08,180 --> 00:06:09,139
How many times have I shown you?

157
00:06:09,180 --> 00:06:11,019
How'd you scrub the crab like this?

158
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,639
Can you even do this job or not?

159
00:06:13,459 --> 00:06:14,300
If you keep slacking off like this,

160
00:06:14,319 --> 00:06:14,800
today I'm

161
00:06:15,019 --> 00:06:15,779
not paying your wages.

162
00:06:16,939 --> 00:06:17,579
What's that supposed to mean?

163
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:18,360
You're gonna stiff me?

164
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:19,660
You promised to pay me.

165
00:06:19,879 --> 00:06:21,000
Come on, what good are you?

166
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,519
You can't even learn to scrub a crab.

167
00:06:22,620 --> 00:06:23,680
Today's pay is definitely docked.

168
00:06:23,839 --> 00:06:24,519
Then I quit.

169
00:06:24,639 --> 00:06:25,500
No pay anyway.

170
00:06:25,660 --> 00:06:26,199
Did you hear?

171
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,399
Apparently Qi Xiaowei

172
00:06:28,420 --> 00:06:29,939
snuck off to town to study painting.

173
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:31,680
His dad found out

174
00:06:31,779 --> 00:06:33,360
and dragged him home, locked him up all day.

175
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:34,860
Didn't even give him a single meal.

176
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,100
Useless at everything he tries.

177
00:06:36,259 --> 00:06:37,399
Has he ever pulled off a single thing?

178
00:06:37,620 --> 00:06:37,939
Wait.

179
00:06:38,540 --> 00:06:39,740
So he really went to study painting?

180
00:06:39,740 --> 00:06:40,060
See?

181
00:06:40,519 --> 00:06:41,360
Lost this customer, didn't you?

182
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:43,079
Wants to learn a real skill, huh?

183
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:45,379
And this sign, too.

184
00:06:45,939 --> 00:06:46,839
What on earth did you paint here?

185
00:06:46,839 --> 00:06:47,779
It's all weird and misshapen.

186
00:06:48,339 --> 00:06:49,379
And it's cross-eyed too.

187
00:06:49,819 --> 00:06:51,120
You did this to spite me, right?

188
00:06:51,620 --> 00:06:52,459
Who's supposed to look at this?

189
00:06:52,660 --> 00:06:53,240
Mister.

190
00:06:55,620 --> 00:06:57,240
Your shop's sign is so unique.

191
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:58,279
It's really well painted.

192
00:06:59,019 --> 00:06:59,500
Xiaofang.

193
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:00,100
Xiaofang's here.

194
00:07:00,819 --> 00:07:01,980
Jingjing, out shopping, are you?

195
00:07:02,439 --> 00:07:03,360
Want something to eat?

196
00:07:03,699 --> 00:07:05,079
So much seafood here, well,

197
00:07:05,220 --> 00:07:05,639
grab some,

198
00:07:05,899 --> 00:07:06,920
steam it up at home.

199
00:07:07,060 --> 00:07:07,899
Right, it's all fresh.

200
00:07:08,180 --> 00:07:09,399
No need, thanks, Auntie.

201
00:07:09,639 --> 00:07:10,519
We'll keep looking around.

202
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:10,959
Let's go.

203
00:07:13,620 --> 00:07:14,139
Big mouth.

204
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:16,240
Trying to give her stuff for free?

205
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:19,699
I was just being polite.

206
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:20,899
Such a cheapskate.

207
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,240
This kid has no sense at all.

208
00:07:46,699 --> 00:07:47,600
Right here.

209
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:49,220
Seven bucks, seven bucks, come on!

210
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:50,800
Wipe this down for me.

211
00:07:51,339 --> 00:07:51,660
Okay.

212
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:52,579
Did you hear me?

213
00:07:53,139 --> 00:07:54,100
Wipe this down for me.

214
00:07:54,819 --> 00:07:55,360
I won't do it.

215
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:57,660
Do it or you're fired.

216
00:08:00,439 --> 00:08:01,079
Coming, coming!

217
00:08:01,939 --> 00:08:02,740
Stop it, stop fighting.

218
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:04,379
Everyone's watching, you know.

219
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:07,879
Such frustrated hopes.

220
00:08:07,939 --> 00:08:08,480
Forty-five.

221
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,959
With your figure, this outfit fits perfectly

222
00:08:24,079 --> 00:08:25,060
It looks so good on you

223
00:08:29,839 --> 00:08:30,540
Let me look around some more

224
00:08:32,299 --> 00:08:33,000
Come back, come back, come back

225
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:33,679
I'll give you a discount

226
00:08:35,860 --> 00:08:36,419
380

227
00:08:37,659 --> 00:08:38,820
You're kidding, lady

228
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,220
Who are you calling "lady"?

229
00:08:40,659 --> 00:08:41,480
Since you said that

230
00:08:41,679 --> 00:08:42,120
180

231
00:08:43,399 --> 00:08:44,379
Come on, let's go

232
00:08:44,919 --> 00:08:46,779
You look pretty good

233
00:08:46,779 --> 00:08:48,059
And you don't look broke either

234
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:50,080
Yet here you are doing cutthroat bargaining

235
00:08:51,940 --> 00:08:54,220
Even with money, you shouldn't waste it

236
00:08:58,940 --> 00:08:59,440
Tell you what

237
00:09:00,919 --> 00:09:01,559
All together

238
00:09:02,620 --> 00:09:03,159
Add 80

239
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:06,399
Come here, kiddo, like this

240
00:09:07,399 --> 00:09:08,080
Just like this

241
00:09:08,340 --> 00:09:09,039
Here, look

242
00:09:09,980 --> 00:09:11,659
Yes, that's right

243
00:09:11,679 --> 00:09:12,220
Like this, like this

244
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:21,720
How much is this malt candy?

245
00:09:22,580 --> 00:09:23,299
Five a stick

246
00:09:23,539 --> 00:09:24,179
Want one?

247
00:09:25,820 --> 00:09:26,519
Too expensive

248
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:27,779
It's not

249
00:09:32,159 --> 00:09:33,100
When I was a kid

250
00:09:33,799 --> 00:09:34,899
It was 20 cents a stick

251
00:09:35,639 --> 00:09:36,860
Well, that was back then

252
00:09:38,860 --> 00:09:39,559
Here, kiddo

253
00:09:49,460 --> 00:09:49,899
Uncle

254
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:51,379
Look, this one

255
00:09:51,879 --> 00:09:52,799
We can buy this

256
00:09:53,539 --> 00:09:54,279
This one works too

257
00:09:56,019 --> 00:09:57,120
Grandpa's seafood stall

258
00:09:57,159 --> 00:09:58,200
Is busy with customers right now

259
00:09:58,460 --> 00:10:00,179
Your mom just had to make me buy you firecrackers

260
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,679
Only 10 yuan worth, got it?

261
00:10:01,919 --> 00:10:03,159
And no making trouble after we buy them

262
00:10:05,779 --> 00:10:06,360
What a coincidence

263
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,580
Run into the Yang family again

264
00:10:08,139 --> 00:10:08,919
You're buying firecrackers too?

265
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:10,399
Boss

266
00:10:10,679 --> 00:10:12,120
give me 10 yuan of pop-its

267
00:10:12,379 --> 00:10:12,659
You got it

268
00:10:14,299 --> 00:10:14,840
10 yuan worth

269
00:10:15,620 --> 00:10:15,960
Bro

270
00:10:16,620 --> 00:10:17,860
This one's great, 480

271
00:10:19,659 --> 00:10:21,059
It's not even New Year's

272
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:23,000
What are you two even up to?

273
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:24,500
Showing off how rich your family is?

274
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:27,539
That's way too cheap

275
00:10:30,019 --> 00:10:31,480
Boss, do you have anything

276
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:32,460
a little pricier?

277
00:10:32,460 --> 00:10:33,059
This is too...

278
00:10:33,639 --> 00:10:35,019
Sure, they're all up on the shelf

279
00:10:35,639 --> 00:10:37,259
Grandpa, let's buy some too

280
00:10:37,340 --> 00:10:38,320
Buy my foot, we're not buying

281
00:10:39,799 --> 00:10:40,879
Hey, boss

282
00:10:41,039 --> 00:10:42,120
Do you have the kind

283
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:43,139
that's super loud?

284
00:10:43,460 --> 00:10:44,779
The kind that dogs

285
00:10:44,799 --> 00:10:45,720
would be scared of

286
00:10:45,899 --> 00:10:46,200
Yes

287
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:47,259
As loud as you want

288
00:10:47,279 --> 00:10:47,700
Let me get it for you

289
00:10:48,620 --> 00:10:49,200
Boss, boss

290
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:50,559
I need to scan the code for my 10 yuan

291
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:51,139
Where do I scan?

292
00:10:51,299 --> 00:10:52,039
I'm busy right now

293
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:53,279
Just take it and let the kid play

294
00:10:53,700 --> 00:10:54,440
What's that supposed to mean?

295
00:10:55,820 --> 00:10:57,320
So 10 yuan doesn't count as money?

296
00:10:57,460 --> 00:10:58,559
You look down on people

297
00:10:58,679 --> 00:10:59,919
How am I looking down on you?

298
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:02,700
My family's got big fireworks

299
00:11:02,860 --> 00:11:04,700
And your family only has tiny pop-its

300
00:11:06,639 --> 00:11:07,899
You really do look down on us

301
00:11:07,919 --> 00:11:08,399
don't you?

302
00:11:08,460 --> 00:11:09,100
Fine, kid

303
00:11:09,460 --> 00:11:09,860
No rush

304
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:11,279
Let me open your eyes

305
00:11:11,519 --> 00:11:11,860
Boss

306
00:11:12,379 --> 00:11:13,820
Give me a string of 100,000-bang ones

307
00:11:14,139 --> 00:11:14,779
100,000-bangs

308
00:11:15,820 --> 00:11:17,139
Grandpa, you're awesome

309
00:11:17,159 --> 00:11:17,960
Of course I am

310
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:18,480
Boss

311
00:11:19,399 --> 00:11:20,940
Get me a 200,000-bang one

312
00:11:21,620 --> 00:11:22,159
Boss

313
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:24,220
Give me two 200,000-bang ones

314
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:25,620
Three

315
00:11:26,179 --> 00:11:26,659
Four

316
00:11:27,340 --> 00:11:27,860
Five

317
00:11:28,039 --> 00:11:28,700
Six

318
00:11:29,039 --> 00:11:29,759
Seven

319
00:11:30,539 --> 00:11:30,919
Eight

320
00:11:31,659 --> 00:11:33,279
Give me a 2,000,000-bang one

321
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:41,080
To drive away the evil

322
00:11:41,419 --> 00:11:42,519
To ward off the ghosts

323
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:51,940
There aren't that many

324
00:11:52,139 --> 00:11:52,620
How about

325
00:11:52,779 --> 00:11:53,960
you just buy the whole lot?

326
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:01,059
What are you trying to do?

327
00:12:01,940 --> 00:12:03,259
What on earth are you up to?

328
00:12:04,139 --> 00:12:05,919
Spending thousands on all these firecrackers

329
00:12:06,059 --> 00:12:07,299
Have you lost your mind, Yang Fanzhu?

330
00:12:07,519 --> 00:12:09,000
You might as well rename yourself Yang Firecracker

331
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:10,500
Where did you get all that money?

332
00:12:11,799 --> 00:12:13,419
My brother insisted on buying them

333
00:12:14,340 --> 00:12:15,059
Where's your brother?

334
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:15,960
Where is he?

335
00:12:16,659 --> 00:12:18,220
On the way home he said

336
00:12:18,559 --> 00:12:20,000
the forest station called him for patrol

337
00:12:20,799 --> 00:12:21,779
Oh, he's a clever one

338
00:12:22,159 --> 00:12:23,440
Knew he'd get scolded coming back

339
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:24,399
so he just slipped away

340
00:12:24,419 --> 00:12:25,340
He bailed, didn't he?

341
00:12:25,860 --> 00:12:27,179
I knew it

342
00:12:27,259 --> 00:12:28,240
Making me take the blame again

343
00:12:28,679 --> 00:12:29,200
Just look at this

344
00:12:29,860 --> 00:12:30,860
This whole family

345
00:12:30,980 --> 00:12:32,159
messing around all day

346
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:33,759
And he's about to become a grandpa

347
00:12:34,740 --> 00:12:36,039
Auntie, you don't know

348
00:12:36,419 --> 00:12:38,440
my uncle Hu was standing up for our family

349
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:38,980
Shut it

350
00:12:39,340 --> 00:12:40,120
This is none of your business

351
00:12:40,679 --> 00:12:42,259
You, why are you yelling

352
00:12:42,259 --> 00:12:43,419
at the kid like that?

353
00:12:43,559 --> 00:12:45,720
And you, Yang Fanmei

354
00:12:46,779 --> 00:12:47,539
Tell me

355
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,720
I gave you money to buy gifts

356
00:12:49,919 --> 00:12:51,179
and what did you come back with?

357
00:12:51,919 --> 00:12:52,379
Take a look

358
00:12:53,379 --> 00:12:54,500
Everyone, take a good look

359
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:56,039
Spent over five hundred yuan

360
00:12:56,179 --> 00:12:57,580
on this piece of junk clothing

361
00:12:58,100 --> 00:12:59,320
And you got a pair of earrings too, huh?

362
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:00,919
They came free

363
00:13:01,679 --> 00:13:02,620
Buy one, get one free

364
00:13:03,460 --> 00:13:05,220
So what if I buy a piece of clothing?

365
00:13:05,659 --> 00:13:06,259
You, you...

366
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:07,600
I bought it with my own money

367
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:08,799
You're way too controlling

368
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:10,120
Your own money?

369
00:13:10,340 --> 00:13:11,399
Every time you see me you cry poor

370
00:13:11,399 --> 00:13:12,240
saying you're broke

371
00:13:12,379 --> 00:13:13,779
saying your husband's business went bust

372
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:15,679
But you've got money for clothes, huh?

373
00:13:16,860 --> 00:13:17,419
Auntie

374
00:13:18,159 --> 00:13:19,399
Little Auntie must have really liked it

375
00:13:19,419 --> 00:13:20,860
that's why she bought it, obviously

376
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:22,539
It's the holiday, after all

377
00:13:22,899 --> 00:13:24,000
Didn't you also tell me and Jingjing

378
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,100
to buy some new clothes?

379
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:25,840
Right

380
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:27,120
Speaking of buying clothes

381
00:13:27,559 --> 00:13:28,039
where are the clothes?

382
00:13:28,940 --> 00:13:30,399
Bring them out, let me see

383
00:13:30,519 --> 00:13:31,159
So where are they?

384
00:13:31,659 --> 00:13:32,919
I didn't see anything I liked

385
00:13:32,940 --> 00:13:33,720
so I didn't buy any

386
00:13:34,799 --> 00:13:35,419
Didn't buy any?

387
00:13:36,179 --> 00:13:37,580
Went and got your nails done instead, huh?

388
00:13:38,059 --> 00:13:38,980
All flashy and gaudy

389
00:13:39,379 --> 00:13:40,220
and pretty expensive too

390
00:13:41,159 --> 00:13:42,039
This cost more than

391
00:13:42,039 --> 00:13:43,059
two hundred fifty yuan, didn't it?

392
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:46,139
You're such a fool

393
00:13:46,440 --> 00:13:47,419
Enough already, Yang Fanyan

394
00:13:47,539 --> 00:13:48,679
Haven't you said enough?

395
00:13:49,039 --> 00:13:49,919
Is there anyone in this family

396
00:13:49,919 --> 00:13:50,779
you haven't scolded yet?

397
00:13:51,399 --> 00:13:51,759
What is it

398
00:13:52,159 --> 00:13:53,480
Does the whole family have to obey

399
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:54,620
your orders and arrangements?

400
00:13:54,779 --> 00:13:55,220
No

401
00:13:56,580 --> 00:13:57,740
I just want to get my nails done

402
00:13:58,220 --> 00:13:59,419
I paid with my own money

403
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:01,279
Did I ask for your money?

404
00:14:01,620 --> 00:14:02,039
I'll give it back to you

405
00:14:02,379 --> 00:14:03,159
I won't take a single cent

406
00:14:39,580 --> 00:14:40,919
Auntie, Auntie, Sis

407
00:14:41,799 --> 00:14:42,299
Sis

408
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:54,240
I

409
00:14:57,080 --> 00:14:58,580
want some malt candy

410
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:02,299
Whenever your grandpa

411
00:15:03,019 --> 00:15:04,240
went to the market

412
00:15:04,679 --> 00:15:07,320
Fanyan would raise her little hand and say

413
00:15:07,759 --> 00:15:09,200
she wanted malt candy

414
00:16:01,379 --> 00:16:02,899
Aren't you thirsty?

415
00:16:03,220 --> 00:16:05,440
Someone hasn't had a drink all afternoon.

416
00:16:05,460 --> 00:16:06,899
Your lips are all cracked.

417
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,179
Aren't you thirsty?

418
00:16:08,179 --> 00:16:10,460
Chrysanthemum tea cools you down.

419
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:14,120
I feel bad for you.

420
00:16:14,960 --> 00:16:15,460
Tell me.

421
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:17,100
How could she treat me like this?

422
00:16:17,580 --> 00:16:20,139
I gave Jingjing money to buy a gift,

423
00:16:20,759 --> 00:16:22,639
and she ended up throwing the money right at me.

424
00:16:23,659 --> 00:16:24,500
What did I do wrong?

425
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:25,700
Am I guilty of something?

426
00:16:26,139 --> 00:16:26,779
Was I wrong?

427
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:27,899
Where did I go wrong?

428
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:28,879
You be the judge here.

429
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:30,799
That's a hard one to judge.

430
00:16:32,399 --> 00:16:33,159
What's that supposed to mean?

431
00:16:34,039 --> 00:16:35,440
I just don't get it, Auntie.

432
00:16:35,539 --> 00:16:37,019
You're the one who gave Jingjing the money.

433
00:16:37,779 --> 00:16:39,039
And you're the one who told her

434
00:16:39,039 --> 00:16:39,820
to spend it however she liked, right?

435
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:41,200
She did exactly that.

436
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:43,059
And you still blew up at her?

437
00:16:45,679 --> 00:16:47,120
The point is her attitude.

438
00:16:47,899 --> 00:16:49,519
I never said she couldn't spend the money.

439
00:16:51,179 --> 00:16:52,159
For all these years,

440
00:16:52,259 --> 00:16:53,320
I say east and she runs west.

441
00:16:54,059 --> 00:16:55,519
She does it on purpose.

442
00:16:55,960 --> 00:16:57,679
Is it easy being her mother?

443
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:00,220
Auntie, how good you are to everyone,

444
00:17:00,539 --> 00:17:01,679
we all know it.

445
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:02,620
We all see it.

446
00:17:02,659 --> 00:17:03,919
And Jingjing knows it too.

447
00:17:04,119 --> 00:17:05,279
She knows you're good to her.

448
00:17:06,039 --> 00:17:07,640
But do you know what she wants?

449
00:17:08,259 --> 00:17:09,220
What does she want?

450
00:17:10,799 --> 00:17:12,259
She wants to drive me crazy.

451
00:17:13,279 --> 00:17:13,940
There you go again.

452
00:17:13,940 --> 00:17:14,539
I'm done talking to you.

453
00:17:14,539 --> 00:17:15,579
Stop, stop, stop.

454
00:17:17,180 --> 00:17:18,660
Come back and sit down, let's chat a bit.

455
00:17:23,460 --> 00:17:24,339
Tell your auntie,

456
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:25,579
what does she really want?

457
00:17:27,140 --> 00:17:29,480
She's definitely not trying to drive you crazy.

458
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:31,519
She wants her grandma to live, of course.

459
00:17:32,440 --> 00:17:33,420
I know.

460
00:17:34,180 --> 00:17:35,880
But the doctor already gave

461
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:37,319
the diagnosis on her grandma's condition.

462
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:39,759
He said no amount of money can cure her.

463
00:17:40,319 --> 00:17:41,599
So isn't that money just wasted?

464
00:17:42,980 --> 00:17:44,200
It's just like getting your nails done.

465
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:45,539
In your eyes, it's all wasted money.

466
00:17:46,019 --> 00:17:47,359
But for Jingjing,

467
00:17:47,480 --> 00:17:48,619
it means a lot.

468
00:18:56,619 --> 00:18:57,900
Careful, the road's slippery

469
00:18:58,099 --> 00:18:59,220
Why did you bring me here?

470
00:18:59,579 --> 00:19:00,460
You'll know once we get there

471
00:19:07,559 --> 00:19:07,960
Look

472
00:19:25,539 --> 00:19:26,319
So beautiful.

473
00:19:31,380 --> 00:19:31,880
Xiaofang.

474
00:19:32,519 --> 00:19:33,539
You once told me,

475
00:19:36,039 --> 00:19:37,339
no matter what others say,

476
00:19:37,980 --> 00:19:38,839
we should always see clearly

477
00:19:38,859 --> 00:19:39,839
what's in our own hearts.

478
00:19:40,819 --> 00:19:42,720
And follow our hearts in everything we do.

479
00:19:43,420 --> 00:19:43,839
Right?

480
00:19:44,700 --> 00:19:45,599
What I mean is,

481
00:19:45,619 --> 00:19:45,960
Fang'er,

482
00:19:50,460 --> 00:19:51,200
these past few weeks,

483
00:19:51,220 --> 00:19:52,359
a lot has happened,

484
00:19:55,519 --> 00:19:56,799
and I did a lot of things wrong.

485
00:19:58,180 --> 00:19:59,279
No matter how you see me now,

486
00:20:00,420 --> 00:20:00,980
I'll accept it.

487
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:02,660
Wrong is wrong.

488
00:20:03,480 --> 00:20:04,960
Even though it was painful,

489
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:06,839
I think all of it

490
00:20:07,099 --> 00:20:08,019
was worth it.

491
00:20:09,740 --> 00:20:11,059
Because now I've seen clearly

492
00:20:11,059 --> 00:20:11,799
what's in my heart.

493
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:13,859
I know exactly what

494
00:20:13,859 --> 00:20:15,240
matters most to me,

495
00:20:16,259 --> 00:20:16,980
what's most important.

496
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:20,000
Xiaofang, it's you.

497
00:20:29,079 --> 00:20:30,180
Yang Xiaofang,

498
00:20:31,220 --> 00:20:32,339
I love you.

499
00:20:33,420 --> 00:20:34,740
I love you.

500
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:37,200
Saranghae.

501
00:20:38,140 --> 00:20:39,319
Je t'aime.

502
00:20:40,140 --> 00:20:41,839
This time I won't back down again.

503
00:20:43,619 --> 00:20:45,500
I'll win your heart once more,

504
00:20:46,440 --> 00:20:47,519
Yang Xiaofang.

505
00:20:48,359 --> 00:20:49,359
I love you.

506
00:20:50,119 --> 00:20:51,619
I love you.

507
00:20:52,720 --> 00:20:54,339
I love you.

508
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:01,019
When did this turn into a soap opera?

509
00:21:15,019 --> 00:21:15,900
Where are you going?

510
00:21:16,839 --> 00:21:17,420
Home.

511
00:21:19,099 --> 00:21:20,119
Home? What for?

512
00:21:21,019 --> 00:21:22,900
Come with me to the hospital to see your grandma.

513
00:21:23,339 --> 00:21:24,819
Let's spend the Mid-Autumn Festival with her.

514
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:27,480
I bought some health supplements.

515
00:21:27,680 --> 00:21:28,900
See if there's anything else we need.

516
00:21:37,319 --> 00:21:39,079
Thank you for all these years

517
00:21:39,140 --> 00:21:40,279
of looking after Jingjing.

518
00:21:40,799 --> 00:21:41,480
Yan'er.

519
00:21:42,539 --> 00:21:43,559
After I'm gone,

520
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:46,319
you must take good care of Jingjing.

521
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:48,119
This child...

522
00:21:49,039 --> 00:21:51,000
It breaks my heart to see her.

523
00:21:51,559 --> 00:21:52,140
Grandma.

524
00:21:53,259 --> 00:21:54,259
What are you talking about?

525
00:21:55,319 --> 00:21:56,680
Didn't we already agree?

526
00:21:56,859 --> 00:21:58,079
We're going on a trip together.

527
00:21:58,539 --> 00:21:59,839
I've already planned the whole route.

528
00:22:00,660 --> 00:22:01,559
As soon as you get better,

529
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:02,559
we'll set off.

530
00:22:03,119 --> 00:22:04,119
All right, all right.

531
00:22:08,319 --> 00:22:09,839
The liver has already failed.

532
00:22:10,339 --> 00:22:11,240
She's very old now.

533
00:22:11,660 --> 00:22:12,559
An organ transplant

534
00:22:12,740 --> 00:22:13,420
would serve no purpose.

535
00:22:14,039 --> 00:22:14,720
Besides,

536
00:22:15,039 --> 00:22:16,380
at her age,

537
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:18,519
the surgical risk is far too high.

538
00:22:19,039 --> 00:22:20,220
It would only add to her suffering.

539
00:22:22,660 --> 00:22:23,299
I understand.

540
00:22:24,640 --> 00:22:25,220
Doctor,

541
00:22:26,160 --> 00:22:26,859
I was wondering,

542
00:22:27,279 --> 00:22:28,799
if there's any other way,

543
00:22:29,700 --> 00:22:30,859
we'd like to try it.

544
00:22:31,559 --> 00:22:32,359
In cases like this,

545
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:34,740
we usually recommend moving to hospice care.

546
00:22:42,599 --> 00:22:43,359
Jingjing.

547
00:22:45,619 --> 00:22:47,799
What I'm saying may be hard to hear,

548
00:22:48,759 --> 00:22:51,099
but it's the truth, no doubt about it.

549
00:22:52,799 --> 00:22:54,319
If you told your grandma

550
00:22:54,380 --> 00:22:55,880
you spent all that money keeping her hospitalized,

551
00:22:56,279 --> 00:22:57,680
she'd surely refuse.

552
00:22:59,359 --> 00:23:00,680
I'm definitely going to borrow the money.

553
00:23:01,420 --> 00:23:02,319
Once I've earned it,

554
00:23:02,740 --> 00:23:04,039
I'll pay you back right away.

555
00:23:04,559 --> 00:23:05,640
If you don't trust me,

556
00:23:05,900 --> 00:23:07,180
I can write you an IOU.

557
00:23:10,700 --> 00:23:12,019
It's not that I'm worried about the money.

558
00:23:14,940 --> 00:23:16,680
Your dad and I divorced so long ago,

559
00:23:17,420 --> 00:23:18,920
and he found you a stepmother.

560
00:23:19,980 --> 00:23:21,539
I'm afraid people will gossip.

561
00:23:22,019 --> 00:23:22,619
And then

562
00:23:22,880 --> 00:23:24,660
it might stir up trouble in their family.

563
00:23:26,660 --> 00:23:28,000
Looks like your whole life,

564
00:23:29,460 --> 00:23:31,299
you just live for what other people say.

565
00:23:32,619 --> 00:23:33,579
That gossip

566
00:23:34,140 --> 00:23:35,019
and my grandma's life,

567
00:23:36,160 --> 00:23:37,079
which one matters more?

568
00:23:38,599 --> 00:23:39,559
Then let me ask you,

569
00:23:41,480 --> 00:23:43,359
if it were you lying there today,

570
00:23:44,660 --> 00:23:45,819
would you want me to do this?

571
00:23:49,859 --> 00:23:50,599
Coming through, coming through!

572
00:24:03,339 --> 00:24:05,759
Since you're putting it that bluntly

573
00:24:06,900 --> 00:24:08,559
then let me make my position clear too

574
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:10,240
If someday

575
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:12,059
I really end up in that state

576
00:24:12,759 --> 00:24:13,599
don't try to resuscitate me

577
00:24:13,859 --> 00:24:14,839
don't put me on tubes

578
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:16,559
Better a short pain than a long one

579
00:24:17,039 --> 00:24:18,799
Just let me go quickly and painlessly

580
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:21,660
so I won't be a burden to you

581
00:24:23,400 --> 00:24:25,279
So you think all of this is a burden

582
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:26,460
right?

583
00:24:27,019 --> 00:24:28,279
You know what I mean

584
00:24:29,279 --> 00:24:29,940
I do

585
00:24:32,740 --> 00:24:33,880
But that's your choice

586
00:24:35,519 --> 00:24:36,339
My choice

587
00:24:38,119 --> 00:24:39,819
is to ease my grandma's suffering

588
00:24:48,700 --> 00:24:49,859
See, now you've hit the real point

589
00:24:50,500 --> 00:24:51,740
It's just like getting your nails done

590
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:53,140
In your eyes it's all a waste of money

591
00:24:53,539 --> 00:24:54,880
But to Jingjing

592
00:24:55,079 --> 00:24:56,180
it means everything

593
00:25:07,619 --> 00:25:09,160
Where are you taking the patient?

594
00:25:09,259 --> 00:25:10,299
She's being moved to another ward.

595
00:25:10,460 --> 00:25:11,799
Another ward? Which one?

596
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:13,319
The hospice ward.

597
00:25:18,019 --> 00:25:20,019
Why are you so stubborn, child?

598
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:22,579
Was everything we just said for nothing?

599
00:25:23,220 --> 00:25:24,359
Everything I do,

600
00:25:24,519 --> 00:25:25,019
it's all for...

601
00:25:25,039 --> 00:25:26,119
For my own good again, right?

602
00:25:26,559 --> 00:25:27,079
No need.

603
00:25:27,440 --> 00:25:28,119
I can handle it myself.

604
00:25:30,779 --> 00:25:31,339
Fine, fine, fine.

605
00:25:32,079 --> 00:25:33,839
I'll go pay for your grandma.

606
00:25:33,980 --> 00:25:34,359
Alright.

607
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:35,359
No need.

608
00:25:37,619 --> 00:25:38,420
I've already paid.

609
00:25:40,039 --> 00:25:40,779
You paid?

610
00:25:41,779 --> 00:25:42,799
Where did you get the money?

611
00:25:43,259 --> 00:25:44,079
It's none of your business.

612
00:25:44,259 --> 00:25:45,119
You don't need to worry about it.

613
00:25:49,619 --> 00:25:50,720
You have to tell me,

614
00:25:51,440 --> 00:25:52,279
where did the money come from?

615
00:26:02,700 --> 00:26:03,839
Back so soon?

616
00:26:13,920 --> 00:26:14,220
Sis.

617
00:26:14,400 --> 00:26:15,099
I'm picking persimmons.

618
00:26:15,220 --> 00:26:15,500
Want some?

619
00:26:16,240 --> 00:26:17,539
Auntie, why are you back?

620
00:26:17,819 --> 00:26:19,460
Weren't you at the hospital with Jingjing?

621
00:26:19,700 --> 00:26:20,920
Why are you back so soon?

622
00:26:28,539 --> 00:26:29,500
What's the point of this dinner?

623
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:30,920
What festival is there to celebrate?

624
00:26:31,500 --> 00:26:31,920
You people...

625
00:26:32,460 --> 00:26:34,000
You all ganged up to fool me.

626
00:26:34,460 --> 00:26:36,220
I'm just an outsider, right?

627
00:26:38,359 --> 00:26:40,359
I finally get a family reunion.

628
00:26:40,819 --> 00:26:43,299
I spent half a month preparing this meal.

629
00:26:43,559 --> 00:26:44,880
What are you doing?

630
00:26:45,240 --> 00:26:46,380
For this family...

631
00:26:46,940 --> 00:26:48,160
I gave up everything.

632
00:26:49,279 --> 00:26:49,740
You people...

633
00:26:50,220 --> 00:26:51,579
You wanted firecrackers.

634
00:26:51,599 --> 00:26:53,119
So I went and got you firecrackers.

635
00:26:53,380 --> 00:26:54,900
You wanted king crab.

636
00:26:54,900 --> 00:26:56,559
So I went and got you king crab.

637
00:26:56,799 --> 00:26:58,200
But how do you treat me?

638
00:26:59,259 --> 00:27:00,900
Jingjing wants to open a nail salon.

639
00:27:01,440 --> 00:27:02,599
Did any of you tell me?

640
00:27:03,319 --> 00:27:04,119
Behind my back.

641
00:27:04,359 --> 00:27:06,019
Pooling money, buying in as partners.

642
00:27:07,660 --> 00:27:08,720
This is how you treat me?

643
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:09,940
Do you have any conscience?

644
00:27:11,680 --> 00:27:12,319
I get it now.

645
00:27:13,019 --> 00:27:13,740
In this household,

646
00:27:14,240 --> 00:27:15,400
you're all one family.

647
00:27:15,619 --> 00:27:16,920
I'm the only outsider.

648
00:27:19,279 --> 00:27:20,019
Say something!

649
00:27:20,640 --> 00:27:22,240
Aren't you usually so quick with words,

650
00:27:22,240 --> 00:27:23,519
so sharp and clever?

651
00:27:23,819 --> 00:27:25,500
Always scheming, always nitpicking.

652
00:27:26,099 --> 00:27:27,519
Why so quiet now?

653
00:27:28,200 --> 00:27:29,140
Has any one of you

654
00:27:29,380 --> 00:27:30,960
ever once thought about me?

655
00:27:31,779 --> 00:27:32,099
You people...

656
00:27:32,799 --> 00:27:33,960
Forget the festival.

657
00:27:34,259 --> 00:27:35,559
Let this family just fall apart!

658
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:36,859
Auntie.

659
00:27:37,539 --> 00:27:38,940
Don't be so angry.

660
00:27:40,299 --> 00:27:40,859
Xiaofang.

661
00:27:41,559 --> 00:27:43,140
This was all your idea, wasn't it?

662
00:27:43,700 --> 00:27:45,400
How have I always treated you?

663
00:27:46,039 --> 00:27:48,299
Heaven sees everything.

664
00:27:49,460 --> 00:27:49,839
You...

665
00:27:50,779 --> 00:27:51,859
You treat me like this.

666
00:27:53,759 --> 00:27:55,259
Where's your conscience?

667
00:27:55,880 --> 00:27:57,420
How can you face me?

668
00:27:58,519 --> 00:27:59,099
Auntie.

669
00:28:00,500 --> 00:28:01,319
It's not like that.

670
00:28:01,859 --> 00:28:02,400
I'm sorry.

671
00:28:03,140 --> 00:28:04,880
I'm sorry, I'm so sorry.

672
00:28:05,099 --> 00:28:06,339
It's all my fault.

673
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:09,180
I took the money everyone gave me

674
00:28:10,900 --> 00:28:12,859
and used it for my grandma's medical bills.

675
00:28:13,259 --> 00:28:13,839
What?

676
00:28:21,839 --> 00:28:22,640
She got hurt.

677
00:28:23,440 --> 00:28:24,220
What happened?

678
00:28:24,759 --> 00:28:26,259
How did she fall down?

679
00:28:31,839 --> 00:28:32,960
Let me see, let me see.

680
00:28:33,519 --> 00:28:34,559
Did you break anything, Jingjing?

681
00:28:34,559 --> 00:28:36,299
What's your grandma's hospital stay to me?

682
00:28:36,480 --> 00:28:37,839
How dare you use my money?

683
00:28:38,039 --> 00:28:39,220
Watch your tone.

684
00:28:39,900 --> 00:28:40,339
Mom.

685
00:28:41,019 --> 00:28:41,740
This is my business.

686
00:28:42,180 --> 00:28:43,019
It's none of yours.

687
00:28:43,099 --> 00:28:43,799
Shut up.

688
00:28:46,259 --> 00:28:47,160
What are you so worked up about?

689
00:28:47,500 --> 00:28:48,339
Obviously!

690
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:49,420
That's my whole retirement savings.

691
00:28:49,420 --> 00:28:50,599
How can I not be worked up?

692
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:52,519
Are you gonna support me in old age?

693
00:28:53,180 --> 00:28:54,859
Jingjing, how could you do this?

694
00:28:55,160 --> 00:28:56,680
You lied and swindled money.

695
00:28:59,720 --> 00:29:00,480
You deserve it.

696
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:05,099
Yang Fanyan.

697
00:29:05,799 --> 00:29:06,539
Say that again.

698
00:29:07,500 --> 00:29:08,519
I said you deserve it.

699
00:29:09,980 --> 00:29:10,779
You deserve it, you deserve it.

700
00:29:11,079 --> 00:29:11,720
You absolutely deserve it.

701
00:29:13,960 --> 00:29:15,339
You're the one who deserves it.

702
00:29:16,140 --> 00:29:17,220
You deserve your divorce.

703
00:29:17,579 --> 00:29:18,880
You deserve Jingjing disowning you as her mom.

704
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:20,160
You deserve Dou Cheng dumping you.

705
00:29:20,440 --> 00:29:22,140
The Maldives, my foot.

706
00:29:22,140 --> 00:29:23,299
A honeymoon trip.

707
00:29:23,700 --> 00:29:24,599
So obsessed with saving face.

708
00:29:24,700 --> 00:29:26,180
Dou Cheng would rather stay with his ex-wife

709
00:29:26,180 --> 00:29:27,000
at the hospital than be with you.

710
00:29:27,140 --> 00:29:28,160
And you still put on a show for us.

711
00:29:44,980 --> 00:29:46,319
You hit me!

712
00:29:46,359 --> 00:29:47,480
Yeah, I hit you!

713
00:29:47,579 --> 00:29:48,960
You loudmouthed jerk!

714
00:29:49,359 --> 00:29:49,940
Why you...

715
00:29:50,279 --> 00:29:51,380
Stop it! Stop hitting!

716
00:29:51,859 --> 00:29:53,119
Quit it! You're hitting me!

717
00:29:55,819 --> 00:29:57,160
I'll hit you, you shameless brat!

718
00:30:01,720 --> 00:30:03,000
You scold me, but was I wrong?

719
00:30:03,019 --> 00:30:04,740
She's your sister!

720
00:30:04,759 --> 00:30:06,279
So what if she's my sister?

721
00:30:09,319 --> 00:30:10,819
So I just have to take it?

722
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:13,799
Mom, you always play favorites!

723
00:30:14,599 --> 00:30:15,359
When I was little,

724
00:30:15,660 --> 00:30:17,579
I got leftovers and hand-me-downs.

725
00:30:18,680 --> 00:30:19,619
When I grew up,

726
00:30:21,380 --> 00:30:23,119
you raised Fanhu's daughter,

727
00:30:23,420 --> 00:30:24,980
always sticking up for Yang Fanyan.

728
00:30:25,500 --> 00:30:26,680
You scraped together every penny

729
00:30:26,839 --> 00:30:28,619
to send Yang Fanzhu to college.

730
00:30:29,039 --> 00:30:30,140
And me?

731
00:30:30,960 --> 00:30:32,599
I didn't even finish high school.

732
00:30:32,599 --> 00:30:33,720
Did you ever care?

733
00:30:33,940 --> 00:30:35,759
How is that my fault?

734
00:30:36,140 --> 00:30:37,160
You didn't go to high school

735
00:30:37,160 --> 00:30:38,799
because you ranked second from the bottom!

736
00:30:39,579 --> 00:30:40,900
because you were busy chasing girls!

737
00:30:41,140 --> 00:30:42,619
So what if I had a girlfriend?

738
00:30:42,619 --> 00:30:44,359
Why do you always think you're right?

739
00:30:44,839 --> 00:30:45,859
Why does everyone in this house

740
00:30:45,859 --> 00:30:46,779
get to lecture me?

741
00:30:47,099 --> 00:30:48,640
I've had such a raw deal!

742
00:30:48,819 --> 00:30:50,319
You've all had it rough,

743
00:30:50,980 --> 00:30:52,619
and only I haven't, right?

744
00:30:53,460 --> 00:30:55,539
I worried myself sick over this family.

745
00:30:55,779 --> 00:30:56,299
And any of you,

746
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:57,759
did you ever say one kind word to me?

747
00:30:57,759 --> 00:30:58,579
Stop it!

748
00:30:59,259 --> 00:31:00,500
Where are your manners?

749
00:31:01,759 --> 00:31:03,839
I'm still standing right here!

750
00:31:03,940 --> 00:31:05,319
Saying all this stuff

751
00:31:05,519 --> 00:31:07,200
right in front of me, what's the point?

752
00:31:07,700 --> 00:31:09,460
Every single one of you,

753
00:31:09,660 --> 00:31:10,880
can't you just let me

754
00:31:10,880 --> 00:31:12,019
worry a little less?

755
00:31:12,539 --> 00:31:14,759
And now you're the ones feeling wronged?

756
00:31:14,859 --> 00:31:16,200
What about how wronged I feel?

757
00:31:17,079 --> 00:31:17,660
All these years,

758
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:19,579
none of you were home.

759
00:31:19,779 --> 00:31:21,059
I'm the one who stayed with Mom!

760
00:31:21,059 --> 00:31:21,660
Stop!

761
00:31:23,559 --> 00:31:24,640
Why did I just wet myself?

762
00:31:41,940 --> 00:31:42,940
Yes, yes, that's right.

763
00:31:43,259 --> 00:31:43,700
Fanzhu.

764
00:31:44,119 --> 00:31:44,660
Don't panic, don't panic.

765
00:31:44,660 --> 00:31:45,380
Did you get through to 120?

766
00:31:45,700 --> 00:31:47,259
Your dad went to get the car.

767
00:31:47,599 --> 00:31:48,140
Go on.

768
00:31:48,240 --> 00:31:49,099
We have our own car.

769
00:31:49,119 --> 00:31:50,240
Once he's here, we'll go.

770
00:31:50,519 --> 00:31:51,880
Come on, take deep breaths.

771
00:31:52,319 --> 00:31:53,420
Grandma, I'm scared.

772
00:31:53,980 --> 00:31:54,539
Don't be scared.

773
00:31:55,420 --> 00:31:56,140
Don't be scared, okay?

774
00:31:56,500 --> 00:31:57,380
Take a deep breath in.

775
00:31:59,440 --> 00:32:00,259
Breathe out slowly.

776
00:32:01,779 --> 00:32:03,140
Yes, that's it, relax your belly.

777
00:32:04,640 --> 00:32:05,160
Relax.

778
00:32:05,259 --> 00:32:05,819
Are you okay?

779
00:32:07,039 --> 00:32:07,759
Listen, you two...

780
00:32:07,779 --> 00:32:08,339
That's about enough.

781
00:32:08,380 --> 00:32:09,359
Hurry and get her to the car.

782
00:32:09,579 --> 00:32:10,480
The guy's waiting in the car.

783
00:32:10,480 --> 00:32:11,160
Let me take her over first.

784
00:32:11,519 --> 00:32:12,240
Quick, quick, quick!

785
00:32:12,680 --> 00:32:14,079
These two okay, Mom?

786
00:32:17,720 --> 00:32:18,160
Yeah.

787
00:32:25,599 --> 00:32:26,440
Don't be nervous, okay?

788
00:32:26,779 --> 00:32:27,380
Um...

789
00:32:27,599 --> 00:32:28,599
We'll be at the hospital soon.

790
00:32:29,059 --> 00:32:29,640
Deep breaths.

791
00:32:30,400 --> 00:32:32,180
But why don't I feel anything now?

792
00:32:32,519 --> 00:32:33,319
Just now, Bite

793
00:32:33,319 --> 00:32:34,700
was kicking like crazy in my belly.

794
00:32:34,700 --> 00:32:35,799
Now he's gone all quiet.

795
00:32:36,039 --> 00:32:37,400
He's just worn out, worn out.

796
00:32:39,519 --> 00:32:41,539
Why do I have to keep lying down?

797
00:32:42,119 --> 00:32:43,400
Your water's already broken.

798
00:32:43,819 --> 00:32:44,900
And we've still got a ways

799
00:32:44,920 --> 00:32:45,980
to go to the hospital.

800
00:32:46,140 --> 00:32:47,160
If all the fluid leaks out,

801
00:32:47,339 --> 00:32:48,500
the baby could suffocate.

802
00:32:48,980 --> 00:32:49,640
Don't be scared, don't be scared.

803
00:32:49,779 --> 00:32:50,779
Lift your legs up a bit.

804
00:32:50,779 --> 00:32:51,200
It's okay.

805
00:32:51,720 --> 00:32:52,500
Slow down, slow down.

806
00:32:52,519 --> 00:32:53,920
Don't jolt the baby out!

807
00:32:54,740 --> 00:32:55,460
What's wrong, what's wrong?

808
00:32:55,759 --> 00:32:56,299
It hurts!

809
00:32:56,480 --> 00:32:57,000
It hurts.

810
00:32:57,180 --> 00:32:57,640
It's okay.

811
00:32:57,640 --> 00:32:58,279
Deep breaths, deep breaths.

812
00:32:58,279 --> 00:32:58,880
Deep breaths.

813
00:32:59,200 --> 00:33:00,579
Giving birth always hurts.

814
00:33:00,680 --> 00:33:01,519
That's it, deep breaths.

815
00:33:03,980 --> 00:33:05,740
Let me peel a tangerine for you.

816
00:33:06,079 --> 00:33:07,099
Are you brain-dead?

817
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:08,480
Can she even eat anything right now?

818
00:33:08,700 --> 00:33:09,339
Then don't eat it.

819
00:33:09,359 --> 00:33:10,819
How'll she have the strength to push later?

820
00:33:11,059 --> 00:33:11,400
Here.

821
00:33:11,859 --> 00:33:12,400
Open up, here.

822
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:14,039
Did you forget?

823
00:33:14,099 --> 00:33:15,240
Back when you had Dandan.

824
00:33:16,220 --> 00:33:17,200
Right, right, she can't eat.

825
00:33:17,880 --> 00:33:18,400
I'll eat it.

826
00:33:18,480 --> 00:33:20,480
Honestly, what a memory.

827
00:33:20,660 --> 00:33:21,819
Totally scatterbrained.

828
00:33:22,220 --> 00:33:22,700
Obviously.

829
00:33:22,799 --> 00:33:23,380
Just like you.

830
00:33:23,380 --> 00:33:24,460
No brains, just sneaky tricks.

831
00:33:24,920 --> 00:33:25,279
Auntie.

832
00:33:25,279 --> 00:33:26,559
What happened when you had Dandan?

833
00:33:27,640 --> 00:33:28,480
She thought she could...

834
00:33:28,480 --> 00:33:29,339
...give birth naturally.

835
00:33:29,480 --> 00:33:30,079
So...

836
00:33:30,099 --> 00:33:31,180
Afraid she'd run out of energy,

837
00:33:31,359 --> 00:33:32,440
she stuffed herself like crazy.

838
00:33:32,559 --> 00:33:33,740
And the result? Let her tell you herself.

839
00:33:34,920 --> 00:33:35,619
Let me tell you,

840
00:33:35,779 --> 00:33:36,900
I really pigged out that day.

841
00:33:37,339 --> 00:33:38,619
That morning I slurped down a bowl of noodles.

842
00:33:38,740 --> 00:33:39,920
Double toppings, double eggs.

843
00:33:39,980 --> 00:33:41,160
Really hit the spot.

844
00:33:41,299 --> 00:33:42,519
By noon I was hungry again.

845
00:33:42,759 --> 00:33:44,480
So I ordered two pounds of crawfish.

846
00:33:44,839 --> 00:33:45,759
Come evening, I figured,

847
00:33:45,759 --> 00:33:46,960
I definitely wasn't giving birth that day.

848
00:33:47,200 --> 00:33:48,599
So I tore into half a braised duck.

849
00:33:48,940 --> 00:33:50,440
Who knew I'd go into labor at midnight?

850
00:33:50,740 --> 00:33:51,920
I was munching on stinky tofu,

851
00:33:52,279 --> 00:33:53,539
and suddenly I couldn't take it.

852
00:33:53,839 --> 00:33:54,920
The baby was coming.

853
00:33:55,420 --> 00:33:56,400
Doctor, I got on the delivery table.

854
00:33:56,500 --> 00:33:57,680
I pushed with all my might.

855
00:33:57,740 --> 00:33:58,920
But it just wouldn't come out.

856
00:34:00,420 --> 00:34:01,160
Then the doctor...

857
00:34:01,920 --> 00:34:02,599
...informed the family.

858
00:34:03,180 --> 00:34:04,619
Said I needed a C-section.

859
00:34:05,079 --> 00:34:06,579
